                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/33.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>691. Referring to my telegram 638, December 6, I took the matter in question up
                    informally with the Foreign Office dwelling on the unconstitutionality of the
                    threat of confiscation and pointed out that writ of amparo would issue as t
                    result of such action by the State Government. The Spanish Minister informs me
                    that the amount of the tax has been reduced to two and a half per cent, the
                    threat of confiscation withdrawn and a long term of easy payment granted which I
                    trust is a satisfactory solution to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
